# Neomutt

My Neomutt setup is quite simple and uses only one email provider: [Fastmail](http://www.fastmail.com).
This dotfiles should work on Linux (I use Arch) and OSX.

## Requirements

- [mbsync](https://isync.sourceforge.io/mbsync.html)
- [msmtp](https://marlam.de/msmtp/)
- [neomutt](https://neomutt.org/)

Misc utils:

- [ranger](https://github.com/ranger/ranger)

## Email provider password setup

Encrypt the email provider password using gpg

`gpg --decrypt -r user@email.com email.secret`

`user@email.com` should be set to a recipient for a key created just for this purpose.

Save the gpg key passphrase 

`echo "{{key passphrase}}" > ~/.passphrase`

Make the passphrase file visible to the current user only

`chmod 600 ~/.passphrase`

## Create symbolic links to dotfiles

`./setup.sh`

